==Trivia== * In ''V-Rally 2'' it has misplaced license plate compared to the real life car.

{{Object | Name=Peugeot 306 MAXI | Guid=3055-7490 | Deck=Based on the 306 S16, the Peugeot 306 Maxi boasts an engine which was designed in line with the unit found in the 406 STW touring car. However, as there were no rules governing maximum engine speed for this class, Peugeot Sport managed to set the limiter beyond 10,000 rpm. As a result this naturally aspirated car produces nearly the same power output as the turbocharged WRC machines (though with substantially less torque). | Characters= | Concepts=Concepts/Licensed_Cars,Concepts/Peugeot,Concepts/Rally | Franchises= | Games=Games/DiRT_4,Games/Dirt_5,Games/DiRT_Rally,Games/Dirt_Rally_2_0,Games/EA_Sports_WRC,Games/Gran_Turismo_2,Games/Michelin_Rally_Masters_Race_of_Champions,Games/Need_for_Speed_V_Rally,Games/Need_for_Speed_V_Rally_2,Games/Pro_Rally,Games/Pro_Rally_2001,Games/RalliSport_Challenge,Games/RalliSport_Challenge_2,Games/Rally_Fusion_Race_of_Champions,Games/Sega_Rally_2,Games/Shox,Games/Top_Drives | Locations=Locations/France | People= | Objects=Objects/Car,Objects/Peugeot_106_MAXI,Objects/Peugeot_206_WRC,Objects/Peugeot_306,Objects/Race_Car,Objects/Renault_5_Maxi_Turbo,Objects/Renault_Maxi_Megane | Image=https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/scale_super/151/1511438/3645572-2192760860-latest.jpg }}
<div id='imageData' data-json='{"infobox":{"file":"3645572-2192760860-latest.jpg","path":"151\/1511438\/","mime":"image\/jpeg","sizes":"scale_small,scale_medium,square_avatar,square_medium,square_mini,square_small,square_tiny,scale_super,scale_large,screen_medium,scale_avatar,screen_kubrick","caption":null},"background":[]}' />
===Gran Turismo 2=== This car is only available in Arcade Mode in the Rally Car class. In order to unlock it, the player must win a race in Arcade Mode on Tahiti Road at normal level or higher.
